{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7,"isBulletin":211},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434","Gentile","2002","\u003Cspan>L. Gentile, «Olumpis Olumpios ed IG, XIV, 434», \u003Ci>Epigraphica\u003C/i> 64 (2002): 224–29\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/CJ9QP78X",[8],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":25,"layoutDesc":28,"handNote":35,"date":127,"places":132,"geo":142,"country":137,"provenance":134,"provenanceGeo":146,"region":149,"settlement":139,"repository":150,"idno":154,"textLang":157,"tmNumber":161,"facsimile":162,"letterHeights":169,"publications":173,"zotero":183,"keywords":193,"html":203,"bibl":204,"bulletinDateSort":209,"citedRangeSort":210,"languageSort":158,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic001259","Statue base in honour of Olympis Mestos",{"_":12},"draft",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"honorific","#function.honorific","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/69.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.html",{"_":23,"type":24,"subtype":25,"resp":26,"ref":27},"breccia","stone.breccia","","#Coccato","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/73.html",{"layout":29},{"p":30,"rs":31,"damage":25},"The inscription is set out over four lines on the front face of the block on its upper half. The text is roughly centred, lines 1-3 filling the face, line 4 a single word approximately centered. Spacing between words is apparent and increases significantly in line 3.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":36,"dimensions":113},[37,38],"The letters are regular and with terminal points rather than serfis, and are inscribed in parts in what is almost a punch style, rather than a chiselled groove. Alpha has broken bar; epsilon has mostly equal legnth cross-bars; theta has a full-width cross bar; kappa has full length bars; mu has vertical first and last, three-quarter length mid-strokes; omicron is full-size; pi has eual length verticals; rho has fair-sized closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom strokes; omega is rhomboid and closed.",{"_":39,"ref":40},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[41,44,47,50,53,56,59,62,65,68,71,74,77,80,83,86,89,92,95,98,101,104,107,110],{"_":42,"target":43},"Α type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type2.html",{"_":45,"target":46},"Ε type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html",{"_":48,"target":49},"Ε type2.3","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html",{"_":51,"target":52},"Ε type2.3.1","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html",{"_":54,"target":55},"Ε type2.3.2","https://kings